Slide 17:
Recursive Factorial
How can we take the large problem and break it up into something smaller?
Can we build up a solution?
With factorial, it is easy to see how to break this down by this equivalence:
	n!	= n * ((n-1) * (n-2) * … * 2 * 1)
		= n * (n-1)!
To compute n!, we can rely on (n-1)!

Slide 18:
